title: 2020 United States House of Representatives elections
2020 United States House of Representatives elections
deleted: Leading up to the 2020 elections, the [[Democratic Party (United States)|Democrats]] were projected by many polls, including [[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]] and independent ones, to expand their House majority by around 15 seats due to the Democratic hate for President [[Donald Trump]] and nationwide attitudes over the [[COVID-19 Hoax]] Which has a recovery rate of about 97%. However, although the Democrats retained control of the House, Republicans exceeded expectations, mostly winning back seats they lost in 2018 and shrinking the Democratic majority overall while successfully defending competitive seats in suburbs that the Democrats had hoped to flip. The Republican performance was attributed to President Trump being on the ballot, leading to unprecedented Republican turnout and enthusiasm.<ref>{{cite news |title=U.S. House Election Results |url=https://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2020/11/03/us/elections/results-house.html |accessdate=10 November 2020 |agency=The New York Times}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://apnews.com/article/election-2020-politics-elections-house-elections-nancy-pelosi-1797f752392d02702429b13b1b16b553|title=Dems clinch House control, but majority likely to shrink|publisher=Associated Press|last=Fram|first=Alan|date=November 10, 2020|accessdate=November 12, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.cnbc.com/2020/11/05/2020-election-results-democrats-to-lose-house-seats-but-keep-majority.html|title=Democrats are projected to lose House seats but keep their majority|publisher=CNBC|last=Pramuk|first=Jacob|date=November 5, 2020|accessdate=November 12, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.cnn.com/2020/11/04/politics/house-race-results-2020/index.html|title=Some House Democrats fall while the party fails to flip some key suburban districts|publisher=CNN|last1=Pathe|first1=Simone|last2=Foran|first2=Clare|last3=Raju|first3=Manu|date=November 5, 2020|accessdate=November 13, 2020}}</ref>
